{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Plugins","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"],"anchor":"Composing-Large-Games","title":"Composing Large Games"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" let a game split its ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"own"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" world across types and packages. A "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"plugin","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" goes one step further: it packages a reusable game "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"system"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — as an importable unit of verbs and rules that any game can opt into. Instead of hand-copying the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buy"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sell"},{"type":"text","text":" logic into every shop game, you write it once as a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and splice it in."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A plugin is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"logic only","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":". It contributes the player-typeable vocabulary a system needs and the rules that react to it, but it owns no rooms, items, or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state of its own. It operates over entities and state the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"host"}]},{"type":"text","text":" game declares, receiving what it needs as parameters. That’s what keeps it portable — it assumes nothing about the host’s world beyond the traits and intents they agree on."}]},{"text":"A plugin is a `GamePlugin`","anchor":"A-plugin-is-a-GamePlugin","type":"heading","level":2},{"code":["struct CommercePlugin: GamePlugin {","    static let buy = Intent(\"buy\")","    static let sell = Intent(\"sell\")","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {","        SyntaxRule(\"buy\",  slots: .direct, intent: Self.buy)","        SyntaxRule(\"sell\", slots: .direct, intent: Self.sell)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"verbs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" both default to empty, so a plugin declares only what it needs. Exposing the intents as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"static let"},{"type":"text","text":" constants lets host rules name the same intents the verbs emit."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"The-host-splices-verbs-and-rules","type":"heading","text":"The host splices verbs and rules"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The host stores the plugin as a plain property and splices its vocabulary into its own "},{"code":"verbs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" block. A plain plugin property is neither a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", nor "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":", so the bootstrap’s reflection walk ignores it — it never becomes an entity and never collides."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".price"},{"type":"text","text":" below is a "},{"code":"TraitKey<Int>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" declared once ("},{"code":"extension TraitKey<Int> { static let price = Self(\"price\") }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") — see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/CustomStateAndTraits"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct LampShop: Game {","    let commerce = CommercePlugin()","    @Global var purse = Purse(coins: 10)          \/\/ the HOST owns the wallet","    let lantern = Item { name(\"brass lantern\"); trait(.price, 5) }","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { commerce.verbs }    \/\/ splice the vocabulary","    \/\/ rules below","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Parameterized-rules-over-host-entities","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Parameterized rules over host entities"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The plugin’s rules need the host’s own lantern and purse — things it can’t know about in advance. So rules that touch host state are exposed as ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"parameterized methods","type":"text"}]},{"text":" returning ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", which the host calls with its own declarations. The wallet is handed in as closures that read and adjust the host’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":"; they run under the live turn, so they see and mutate state exactly as an inline rule would."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["extension CommercePlugin {","    @RuleBuilder","    func purchase(","        of item: Item,","        balance: @escaping @Sendable () -> Int,","        charge:  @escaping @Sendable (Int) -> Void","    ) -> Rules {","        item.before(Self.buy) {","            let price = item[.price] ?? 0","            guard balance() >= price else {","                try refuse(\"You can't afford the \\(item.name); it costs \\(price) coins.\")","            }","            charge(price)","            try reply(\"You buy the \\(item.name) for \\(price) coins. You have \\(balance()) left.\")","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ in the host:","var rules: Rules {","    commerce.purchase(of: lantern,","                      balance: { purse.coins },","                      charge:  { purse.coins -= $0 })","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The protocol’s own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":" requirement is for self-contained, world-scoped rules that need nothing from the host; anything host-specific goes through a factory method like this.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"A plugin can contribute only vocabulary","anchor":"A-plugin-can-contribute-only-vocabulary"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The rules are optional. A plugin can teach the parser a word and leave the behavior to the host, which handles the shared intent in its own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct Appraiser: GamePlugin {","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {","        SyntaxRule(\"appraise\", slots: .direct, intent: Intent(\"appraise\"))","    }","}","","\/\/ in the host:","var rules: Rules {","    gem.before(Intent(\"appraise\")) {","        try reply(\"The \\(gem.name) is worth \\(gem[.price] ?? 0) coins.\")","    }","}"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Content-bearing-plugins-own-their-region","type":"heading","text":"Content-bearing plugins own their region"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A logic-only "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" declares no world of its own — it operates entirely over entities the host passes it. A plugin that needs to ship its ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"own"}]},{"text":" rooms, items, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" state is a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" instead: a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" carries "},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"code":"verbs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and the bootstrap discovers its entities by reflection, ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"namespacing"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"namespacing"},{"type":"text","text":" them under the bundle so a reusable plugin can’t collide with the host. List it in the game’s "},{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The two roles compose in one type. A single struct can conform to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"text":" (for its auto-namespaced region and self-contained rules) ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" expose host-facing rule factories exactly like a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"},{"text":" — factories are just methods returning ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", so any type can offer them:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct ShrineContent: GameContent {","    static let donate = Intent(\"donate\")","","    let shrine = Location { name(\"Stone Shrine\"); description(\"…\") }   \/\/ its own room","    @Global var visits = 0                                             \/\/ its own state","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { SyntaxRule(\"donate\", slots: .direct, intent: Self.donate) }","    var rules: Rules { shrine.onEnter { visits += 1; try reply(\"…\") } }  \/\/ self-contained","","    \/\/ Host-facing factory over a host item + host global — the GamePlugin pattern.","    func offering(of item: Item,","                  merit: @escaping @Sendable () -> Int,","                  credit: @escaping @Sendable (Int) -> Void) -> Rules {","        item.before(Self.donate) { credit(item[.value] ?? 0)","            try reply(\"Your merit rises to \\(merit()).\") }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The host lists it in "},{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (registering the namespaced region) ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" splices the factory into its own "},{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", wiring it to host declarations:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct PilgrimGame: Game {","    let shrineKit = ShrineContent()","    @Global var merit = 0","    let coin = Item { name(\"brass coin\"); trait(.value, 7) }","","    var content: GameContents { shrineKit }","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { shrineKit.verbs }","    var rules: Rules {","        shrineKit.offering(of: coin, merit: { merit }, credit: { merit += $0 })","    }","    \/\/ map: place coin in shrineKit.shrine, wire plaza ↔ shrineKit.shrine, …","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"References stay token-based across the boundary, so a host item can sit in a plugin room and a plugin rule can hook a host entity regardless of the namespace."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Worked-examples","text":"Worked examples","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/CommerceGame.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the logic-only commerce plugin (","type":"text"},{"code":"buy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sell"},{"type":"text","text":" verbs, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"purchase"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sale"},{"text":" factories, ","type":"text"},{"code":"LampShop","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" host); ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PluginTests"},{"type":"text","text":" drives a buy\/sell turn end to end."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/ShrineContent.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — the content-bearing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShrineContent"},{"text":" plugin (owns a namespaced shrine region ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" exposes an "},{"code":"offering","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" factory) with its "},{"code":"PilgrimGame","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" host; "},{"code":"ContentPluginTests","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" drives a donate turn across the namespace boundary and checks the namespacing."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}],"role":"symbol","title":"Item","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item","abstract":[{"text":"A thing in the world.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/CustomStateAndTraits":{"title":"Custom State and Traits","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/CustomStateAndTraits","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Carry your own data on entities and in globals, alongside the engine’s closed core."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/customstateandtraits"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GameContents","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The collected content bundles a game declares, in declaration order.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontents","title":"GameContents","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle":{"title":"EntityIDs are namespaced by the bundle","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","abstract":[],"kind":"section","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Rules":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rules","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected rules of a game, declared in one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" block. Large games"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compose: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var rules: Rules { cloakRules; barRules }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Rules","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Rules","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/rules","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location":{"title":"Location","abstract":[{"text":"A place in the world.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Location"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Location","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","kind":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles":{"role":"article","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","type":"topic","title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles","abstract":[{"text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContent":{"abstract":[{"text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","title":"GameContent","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GameContent","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent","type":"topic"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","type":"topic","title":"Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles":{"abstract":[{"text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","title":"Content Bundles","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles","type":"topic","role":"article"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"role":"symbol","title":"GamePlugin","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin","abstract":[{"text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"importable unit of ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}]},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}]}}}